Sec. 14.075. PENALTY FOR FRAUDULENTLY ISSUING A SCALE WEIGHT
TICKET OR RECEIPT. (a) A person commits an offense if the person
fraudulently issues or aids in fraudulently issuing a receipt or
scale weight ticket knowing that it contains a false statement.
(b) An offense under this section is a felony of the second
degree.
Renumbered from Sec. 14.031 and amended by Acts 2001, 77th Leg., ch.
1124, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 2001.

